# Augustus Trading — Crontab Example
# ====================================
# Copy the lines you want to your crontab: crontab -e
#
# The production system uses 3 layers:
#   1. Sentinel: every 15 min (portfolio monitoring + trade dispatch)
#   2. Stop-loss watchdog: every 5 min (position protection)
#   3. S²-MAD: 4x daily at 9,12,15,21 (deeper hybrid analysis)
#
# Adjust the INTERVAL and PATH variables to match your setup.

AUGUSTUS_PATH=/home/user/augustus-trading
PYTHON=/usr/bin/python3

# ─── Layer 1: Trading Runner (every 15 min) ─────────────────────────────────
# Monitors portfolio, dispatches LLM analysis, executes trades.
# Change the interval by modifying the first field (*/15).
# For more aggressive trading: */10 (every 10 min)
# For conservative: */30 (every 30 min)
*/15 * * * * cd $AUGUSTUS_PATH && $PYTHON runner.py --mode full >> logs/runner.log 2>&1

# ─── Layer 2: Stop-Loss Watchdog (every 5 min) ──────────────────────────────
# Protects open positions. Runs independently of the trading layer.
# Recommended: keep at 5 min for safety.
*/5 * * * * cd $AUGUSTUS_PATH && $PYTHON runner.py --mode stop-loss >> logs/stoploss.log 2>&1

# ─── Layer 3: Deep Analysis (4x daily) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Runs at market open (EU), US pre-market, US open, Asia open (UTC).
# Use --regime auto for market regime detection, or override with --regime bull/bear.
0 9,12,15,21 * * * cd $AUGUSTUS_PATH && $PYTHON runner.py --mode full >> logs/runner.log 2>&1

# ─── Optional: Quick Portfolio Check (hourly) ───────────────────────────────
# Just checks balances without LLM calls. Good for monitoring.
0 * * * * cd $AUGUSTUS_PATH && $PYTHON runner.py --mode quick >> logs/quick.log 2>&1
